<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN281-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – kāñci; tuṟai – pēykkāñci. aricilkiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN281">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>tīṅkaṉi yiravamoṭu vēmpumaṉaic cerīi</l>
<l>vāṅkumarup piyāḻoṭu palliyaṅ kaṟaṅkak</l>
<l>kaipayap peyarttu maiyiḻu tiḻuki</l>
<l>yaiyavi citaṟi yāmpa lūti</l>
<l>yicaimaṇi yeṟintu kāñci pāṭi</l>
<l>neṭunakar varaippiṟ kaṭinaṟai pukaiik</l>
<l>kākkam vammō kātalan tōḻi</l>
<l>vēntuṟu viḻuman tāṅkiya</l>
<l>pūmpoṟik kaḻaṟkā ṉeṭuntakai puṇṇē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Inserting in the house [the leaves of] Neem wood along with sweet-fruited ironwood,</l>
<l>while many instruments sound along with the lute with a curved neck,</l>
<l>removing the yield(?) with the hand, smearing black fat,</l>
<l>scattering white mustard seed, blowing the [flute tuned to] Āmpal,</l>
<l>shaking sounding bells, singing the Kāñci,</l>
<l>fumigating with scented fragrance the borders of the tall mansion,</l>
<l>let us protect it, come, beloved friend,</l>
<l>the wound of the paragon on the leg with an flower-dotted anklet</l>
<l>that endured [sharing] the distress suffered by the king.   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
